A real time monitor for PHP applicacions using node.js and WebSockets

Starting the server:

$ node server.js
HTTP server started at 127.0.0.1::5672
Web Socket server started at 127.0.0.1::8880

PHP application configuration
place this code at the beggining of the script:

include('NodeLog.php');
NodeLog::init('127.0.0.1', 5672); // ip and port of the node.js http server

Web interface based on nodejs.org chat demo (http://chat.nodejs.org/)

